      <media id="id14316016_media" alt="">
        <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics12-cceb.png" id="id14316016__onlineimage" height="26" width="103"/>
      </media>
    </figure>
    <figure id="id3907507">
      <media id="id3907507_media" alt="">
        <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics13-1fef.png" id="id3907507__onlineimage" height="24" width="291"/>
      </media>
    </figure>
    <para id="id13938693">When quality factor Q of the tank circuit =∞, the circuit is purely reactive and there is no dissipation.</para>
    <para id="id13896131">When quality factor Q is finite say 1000 then an equivalent R<sub>P</sub> comes in parallel with the tank circuit. R<sub>P </sub>accounts for the losses</para>
    <figure id="id9539070">
      <media id="id9539070_media" alt="">
        <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics14-0f54.png" id="id9539070__onlineimage" height="24" width="90"/>
      </media>
    </figure>
    <para id="id15341467">For a finite quality factor tank circuit, the effective impedance is a pure resistance R<sub>P</sub> at resonance frequency.</para>
    <para id="id14023496">Hence <figure id="id13888419"><media id="id13888419_media" alt=""><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics15-7437.png" id="id13888419__onlineimage" height="24" width="118"/></media></figure></para>
    <para id="id3901794">Frequency response of the tank circuit is :</para>
    <para id="id14026062">
      <figure id="id14026067">
        <media id="id14026067_media" alt="">
          <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics16-66bd.png" id="id14026067__onlineimage" height="24" width="164"/>
        </media>
      </figure>
    </para>
    <figure id="id9037389">
      <media id="id9037389_media" alt="">
        <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics17-c331.png" id="id9037389__onlineimage" height="392" width="626"/>
      </media>
    </figure>
    <para id="id3903154">
      <emphasis effect="bold">Figure4. The peak response of a tank circuit for various quality factors.</emphasis>
    </para>
    <figure id="id8992465">
      <media id="id8992465_media" alt="">
        <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics18-cfb0.png" id="id8992465__onlineimage" height="24" width="134"/>
      </media>
    </figure>
    <figure id="id9016387">
      <media id="id9016387_media" alt="">
        <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics19-0ac5.png" id="id9016387__onlineimage" height="39" width="56"/>
      </media>
    </figure>
    <para id="id3028400">At Q=∞, spike response.</para>
    <para id="id14111257">At Q=finite, peak response.</para>
    <para id="id14111261">As Q falls, sharpness of the peak response is lost.</para>
    <para id="id9017400">
